Dirk Lotriet, News24 (Shutterstock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Bloemfontein - Eighty pupils at a school near Bloemfontein were treated for&nbsp;suspected food poisoning on Thursday morning.Netcare 911&rsquo;s Chris Botha told News24 they were called&nbsp;to the school after a lot of the children became ill.&ldquo;They showed symptoms of food poisoning and we treated them&nbsp;at the school in Botshabelo. The provincial services&rsquo; ambulances also showed up, which was a great help as we had our hands full with such a number of sick&nbsp;children. The children were then taken to hospitals in the area.&rdquo;Botha says that the children attended a funeral on Wednesday,&nbsp;where they ate. &ldquo;There was one pupil who was badly dehydrated, but&nbsp;the rest were OK,&rdquo; Botha said.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.